article.headline: Fresno St. 56, Air Force 41
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. -- Kyle Johnson scored 21 points, helping Fresno State pick up a 56-41 victory over Air Force on Saturday night. Allen Huddleston added 11 points for Fresno State (10-18, 4-11 Mountain West). Kevin Foster grabbed eight rebounds for the Bulldogs, helping the team secure a 44-30 advantage on the boards. Fresno State, however, couldn't connect from 3-point range, hitting just 2 of 14. Air Force (16-11, 7-7) also struggled from long range, making just 4 of 20. And Air Force could only muster 27.9 percent shooting from the floor on the night. Mike Fitzgerald scored 11 points for the Falcons, including a pair of 3-pointers. He was the only player to score in double figures.
